title: Want To Buy:  ISO 1911 Custom Build
postcontent:
Option A:  Frame milled from stock and I choose my own serial number by incorporating my initials into it.

Option B:  Pre-serialized frame from Essex, Caspian, etc.

--I want reliability over accuracy--the gun will be part of my EDC rotation.
--Use whichever frame and slide you deem the best for the build.
--Let's go with all Wilson Combat internals, controls, and parts.
--Commander size.
--Stainless.
--45ACP.
--Accepts 7 round (flush) and 8 round (extended) mags.
--Beavertail.
--Flat MSH.
--Series 70.
--Skeletonized hammer and trigger.
--Rear slanted cocking serrations only.
--Simple custom engraving or rollmarks to denote uniqueness.
--NO FLGR, NO RAIL, NO POLYMER/PLASTIC, NO FCS, NO EXTERNAL EXTRACTOR, NO AMBI-SAFETY, NO DOUBLE STACK MAG, NO DAT

--Original stock size for slide stop, safety, and mag release button (I do not want or need anything extended in size.)
--Three dot sight system similar in style to that found on the Ruger SR1911CMD.

--Finish would be a dull or brushed stainless that is easy to care for and can be buffed if necessary to remove scratches.

--Grips would be wood with a similar engraving that you have already done for me (USN ANCHOR with initials, etc.)

As for rollmarks and engraving:

--On the forward part of the frame, left side, 1 OF 1
--On the forward part of the frame, right side, 1 OF 1 (aligned with same 1 OF 1 on left side.)

--On left side of slide, centered between muzzle and cocking serrations, CUSTOM 1911 45ACP
--On right side of slide, directly below ejection port, JMC ELITE
--On right side of slide, forward of ejection port and higher on the slide than JMC ELITE with larger font, NAVY CHIEF

Note:  CUSTOM 1911 45 ACP and NAVY CHIEF would be of the same font style and size.
Note:  JMC ELITE would be of smaller font size than CUSTOM 1911 45ACP and NAVY CHIEF.
Note:  1 OF 1 would be of the same font style and size and the same distance from the muzzle end on the frame for both sides.
Note:  Font style would be of a BLOCK type.
